        "qnum":  35,
        "question":  "Increased income has been shown to significantly increase life satisfaction in which of the following circumstances?",
        "choices":  [
                        "The increase is attained as a result of a promotion at work",
                        "The individual feels they have earned the increase in income",
                        "The individual donates the amount of the increase to charity",
                        "The increase lifts the individual out of extreme poverty",
                        "The increase allows the individual to save money for emergencies"
                    ],
        "choiceLetters":  [
                              "A",
                              "B",
                              "C",
                              "D",
                              "E"
                          ],
        "correctLetter":  "D",
        "answerText":  "The increase lifts the individual out of extreme poverty",
        "explanation":  "Increase in income has a small correlation to life satisfaction with one exception--when the increase allows the person to be able to meet their basic needs. Once the person is no longer in extreme poverty, employment and engagement on the job are much more strongly correlated with happiness. (1091)"
